fields.name: Avocado
fields.description: The avocado is a tree, long thought to have originated in South Central Mexico, classified as a member of the flowering plant family Lauraceae.

fields.name: Banana
fields.description: A banana is an edible fruit, botanically a berry, produced by several kinds of large herbaceous flowering plants in the genus Musa.

fields.name: Onion
fields.description: The onion also known as the bulb onion or common onion, is a vegetable that is the most widely cultivated species of the genus Allium.

fields.name: Potato
fields.description: The potato is a starchy, tuberous crop from the perennial nightshade Solanum tuberosum
